headline: Stocks to Watch Friday: Nike, JPMorgan, Xiaomi, MP Materials
summary: ↗️ Nike (NKE): The sportswear company said it expects tariffs to raise its annual costs by $1 billion this fiscal year. Shares jumped 10% in premarket trading, however, as its quarterly earnings and sales topped expectations.

headline: Here’s what Wall Street is saying about Nike ahead of Q4 earnings
summary: Nike (NKE) is expected to report results on its fiscal fourth quarter on Thursday, June 26, with a conference call scheduled for 5:00 pm EDT. What to watch for: GUIDANCE: In March, Nike forecast fourth quarter revenue down in the low- to mid-teens, with gross margin down 400-500 basis points.
